Rachel Mair.

00:41:01.260 --> 00:41:04.260
Oh, I can't remember the other one's name.

00:41:04.260 --> 00:41:08.260
So there were chances for girls to go on to be...

00:41:08.260 --> 00:41:12.260
Oh yes, four women because I was asked to become one.

00:41:12.260 --> 00:41:15.260
I was asked to become one.

00:41:15.260 --> 00:41:16.260
Like I say, if I'd have...

00:41:16.260 --> 00:41:20.260
The paperwork had just with me, if I could have done the paperwork.

00:41:20.260 --> 00:41:22.260
I'd have been a boss then by now.

00:41:22.260 --> 00:41:23.260
Sure you would.

00:41:23.260 --> 00:41:27.260
Yes, because I'd have liked to have done something.

00:41:27.260 --> 00:41:29.260
It was just that...

00:41:29.260 --> 00:41:32.260
Did you find the work run out in us then?

00:41:32.260 --> 00:41:37.260
No, not really because I had fun doing it, you know.

00:41:37.260 --> 00:41:39.260
I used to take pride in my work.

00:41:39.260 --> 00:41:43.260
And the quicker I could go and do it perfectly, the better I felt.

00:41:43.260 --> 00:41:44.260
And you could earn more money.

00:41:44.260 --> 00:41:48.260
And I could earn more money until they stopped the piecework.

00:41:48.260 --> 00:41:51.260
Were there some girls who couldn't do the work?

00:41:51.260 --> 00:41:58.260
Because you obviously got really high practical skills on the show.

00:41:58.260 --> 00:42:00.260
But some people are hopeless, I'd be hopeless.

00:42:00.260 --> 00:42:04.260
Yes, so we did have some men and I trained like them.

00:42:04.260 --> 00:42:06.260
I was terrible.

00:42:06.260 --> 00:42:08.260
I shouldn't have I suppose.

00:42:08.260 --> 00:42:11.260
But if I'd seen somebody slacking, I'd go and help them.

00:42:11.260 --> 00:42:13.260
If I could see them, I couldn't do work.

00:42:13.260 --> 00:42:15.260
Because I trained a lot of people there.

00:42:15.260 --> 00:42:17.260
I trained my mother-in-law for one.

00:42:17.260 --> 00:42:19.260
Because she used to gas weld.

00:42:19.260 --> 00:42:21.260
My mother-in-law worked there before me.

00:42:21.260 --> 00:42:24.260
Well, I trained her because the gas welding was finished in.

00:42:24.260 --> 00:42:27.260
So I trained her to see how to weld.

00:42:27.260 --> 00:42:29.260
I trained Valisante, I trained loads of people there.

00:42:29.260 --> 00:42:31.260
Did you get extra money then for that?

00:42:31.260 --> 00:42:33.260
Well, yes.

00:42:33.260 --> 00:42:36.260
When I put in for it, I used to forget to put in for it.

00:42:36.260 --> 00:42:38.260
Because I was having so much fun doing it.

00:42:38.260 --> 00:42:41.260
I used to work as well and train them.

00:42:41.260 --> 00:42:43.260
Or they were getting their money's worth out of me.

00:42:43.260 --> 00:42:45.260
They had their money's worth out of me.

00:42:45.260 --> 00:42:51.260
If I never had another thing, they've had goods 40 years out of me then.

00:42:51.260 --> 00:42:54.260
Do you know we were talking about management earlier?

00:42:54.260 --> 00:42:59.260
And you were saying there were very few managers there at the beginning.

00:42:59.260 --> 00:43:01.260
Is that something that grew then?

00:43:01.260 --> 00:43:03.260
Yes, it did.

00:43:03.260 --> 00:43:05.260
Why is that then?

00:43:05.260 --> 00:43:07.260
I don't know.

00:43:07.260 --> 00:43:09.260
We had one big manager.

00:43:09.260 --> 00:43:13.260
Then I think there was one for each of the sections.

00:43:13.260 --> 00:43:15.260
But then you had a manager.

00:43:15.260 --> 00:43:19.260
You had his understudy, which was a...

00:43:19.260 --> 00:43:22.260
What they call them, I forget what they call them now.

00:43:22.260 --> 00:43:24.260
Like an undermanager or something.

00:43:24.260 --> 00:43:26.260
Yes, yeah, undermanagers.

00:43:26.260 --> 00:43:34.260
But when I finished up there, you had team leaders and line leaders and line feeders.

00:43:34.260 --> 00:43:36.260
Do you think that was unnecessary?

00:43:36.260 --> 00:43:38.260
I think it's really stupid.

00:43:38.260 --> 00:43:41.260
The idea of that was Japanese.

00:43:41.260 --> 00:43:51.260
They wanted them to do work, take over when somebody was going off the line and things like that.

00:43:51.260 --> 00:43:55.260
And that's what they should have been doing.

00:43:55.260 --> 00:43:58.260
But they weren't. They took it too serious.

00:43:58.260 --> 00:44:04.260
They were doing all the sitting back and letting you do everything.

00:44:04.260 --> 00:44:08.260
But if you'd gone and tell them, look, I've got to go, well, go then.

00:44:08.260 --> 00:44:10.260
No, we'll carry on.

00:44:13.260 --> 00:44:15.260
So I think it was unnecessary.

00:44:15.260 --> 00:44:19.260
Because they get paid a lot as well for not contributing that much.

00:44:19.260 --> 00:44:21.260
Don't treat them like we are.

00:44:21.260 --> 00:44:23.260
Don't they? It's a big wage to pay.

00:44:23.260 --> 00:44:25.260
It was, it's stupid.

00:44:25.260 --> 00:44:28.260
And I think they're still doing it today.

00:44:28.260 --> 00:44:31.260
Because if it works in Japan, it doesn't work here.

00:44:31.260 --> 00:44:35.260
Different culture, different people, isn't it?

00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:39.260
So were there skilled jobs there and unskilled jobs?

00:44:39.260 --> 00:44:44.260
Were there different degrees of skill needed for different jobs there?

00:44:44.260 --> 00:44:47.260
Well, you could have done your training.

00:44:47.260 --> 00:44:52.260
I could have gone on to do special skills in Wellington.

00:44:52.260 --> 00:44:56.260
But I didn't want to. I was quite happy doing what I was doing.

00:44:56.260 --> 00:44:58.260
Why is that then?

00:44:58.260 --> 00:45:02.260
But at the end of the day, we were all doing the same job anyway.

00:45:02.260 --> 00:45:05.260
And they didn't, I don't think they recognised it there.

00:45:05.260 --> 00:45:11.260
But you could have gone somewhere else to do if you'd not made well done, what was the other one?

00:45:11.260 --> 00:45:13.260
Co-did well done.

00:45:13.260 --> 00:45:17.260
You know, some of the boys could have gone on to do that.

00:45:17.260 --> 00:45:21.260
And saying that, some of the boys came there with co-did well done and doing ordinary jobs.

00:45:21.260 --> 00:45:24.260
So I don't think it made any difference.

00:45:24.260 --> 00:45:26.260
But you could still make good money.

00:45:26.260 --> 00:45:27.260
Yes.

00:45:27.260 --> 00:45:29.260
There were apprentices there, were there?

00:45:29.260 --> 00:45:36.260
Yes, apprentices there for tool setting, electricians, fitters.

00:45:36.260 --> 00:45:39.260
Yes, there were quite a few apprentices.

00:45:39.260 --> 00:45:41.260
And they were always boys, were they? Young boys?

00:45:41.260 --> 00:45:44.260
No, we had some girls. We had girls electricians.

00:45:44.260 --> 00:45:46.260
Oh, did you? Oh, I didn't know that.

00:45:46.260 --> 00:45:48.260
Yes, we had a few.

00:45:49.260 --> 00:45:53.260
But that's not something that would have appealed to you if you had been different?

00:45:53.260 --> 00:45:57.260
No, no. I was quite happy doing what I was doing.

00:45:57.260 --> 00:46:01.260
Because I went on to do different jobs then after the welding finished.

00:46:01.260 --> 00:46:03.260
I went on to soldering.

00:46:03.260 --> 00:46:05.260
In a way, I enjoyed soldering.

00:46:05.260 --> 00:46:10.260
Which job did you enjoy the best then? Out of all the jobs you did there?

00:46:10.260 --> 00:46:12.260
Out of all the jobs.

00:46:12.260 --> 00:46:16.260
Well, let's see, I enjoyed welding because I was good at it.

00:46:16.260 --> 00:46:19.260
I enjoyed it when I done it.

00:46:21.260 --> 00:46:25.260
So how did the men and the women get on then, do you think?

00:46:25.260 --> 00:46:27.260
Oh, pretty good.

00:46:27.260 --> 00:46:31.260
Because I think half of them married one another anyway.

00:46:31.260 --> 00:46:33.260
They were quite...

00:46:33.260 --> 00:46:35.260
But a lot of them had met there?

00:46:35.260 --> 00:46:37.260
Their partners there.

00:46:37.260 --> 00:46:44.260
So when I saw you in Pont d'Aberin before, you were talking about an initiation ceremony you had.

00:46:44.260 --> 00:46:46.260
Yes, yes.

00:46:46.260 --> 00:46:48.260
Can you tell me about that?

00:46:48.260 --> 00:46:50.260
I was married then, men.

00:46:50.260 --> 00:46:52.260
So my husband knew what I was doing.

00:46:52.260 --> 00:46:54.260
He knows what I'm like.

00:46:54.260 --> 00:46:59.260
So if the boys would come in, no new boys, they'd say, you've got to go and see Yvonne by then now.

00:46:59.260 --> 00:47:02.260
What for? You've got an initiation, please.

00:47:02.260 --> 00:47:05.260
So the boys would come up to me and I'd say, bend over.

00:47:05.260 --> 00:47:07.260
What for? What for?

00:47:07.260 --> 00:47:09.260
Bend over and I'd just go, dooooo.

00:47:09.260 --> 00:47:11.260
I'd give them a little tickle.

00:47:11.260 --> 00:47:13.260
You're alright, boy. You can go.

00:47:13.260 --> 00:47:15.260
They'd be going out of there with red faces.

00:47:15.260 --> 00:47:17.260
I'd be dead today.

00:47:17.260 --> 00:47:20.260
You know, but I'd play play. I never touched them, I.

00:47:20.260 --> 00:47:22.260
It was only a little tease.

00:47:22.260 --> 00:47:25.260
It was never, I'd never put my hands on their little woolies.

00:47:25.260 --> 00:47:27.260
What people thought I was doing, men.

00:47:27.260 --> 00:47:32.260
Because I had one chap, he was a big rugby player.

00:47:32.260 --> 00:47:37.260
And he was scared stiff of me running round the factory rather than standing by me.

00:47:37.260 --> 00:47:39.260
You didn't chase after him, did you?

00:47:39.260 --> 00:47:42.260
No, no. I did sometimes.

00:47:42.260 --> 00:47:45.260
But we had some fun. It was good fun, weren't it?

00:47:45.260 --> 00:47:47.260
Well, there are lots of different things like that.

00:47:47.260 --> 00:47:51.260
You know, were there initiation ceremonies for any of the girls?

00:47:51.260 --> 00:47:54.260
Or if somebody was getting married, was there anything like that?

00:47:54.260 --> 00:47:56.260
Oh yes, oh yes. You'd have hammering if you were getting married.

00:47:56.260 --> 00:47:58.260
They'd put you in a pallet.

00:47:58.260 --> 00:48:02.260
Put all stuff over you. They'd cover you with flour, eggs.

00:48:02.260 --> 00:48:04.260
Curry powder, jam.

00:48:04.260 --> 00:48:07.260
Put condoms on you. Oh yes.

00:48:07.260 --> 00:48:10.260
Was this for the girls or for the boys now?

00:48:10.260 --> 00:48:12.260
For both. It was for both.

00:48:12.260 --> 00:48:15.260
And sometimes they'd put a ball and chain on the men.

00:48:15.260 --> 00:48:17.260
Oh, jeez.

00:48:17.260 --> 00:48:19.260
Yeah, balls and chains on the men, wouldn't they?

00:48:19.260 --> 00:48:22.260
Always, you don't have some fun then.

00:48:22.260 --> 00:48:27.260
Can you remember how much you were paid when you started there?

00:48:27.260 --> 00:48:30.260
I'm sure it was £3.

00:48:30.260 --> 00:48:34.260
From the £3 mark when you first started.

00:48:34.260 --> 00:48:36.260
But like I'm saying, you were having piecework.

00:48:36.260 --> 00:48:39.260
Once you were done your six weeks.

00:48:39.260 --> 00:48:42.260
You had six weeks training as they called it.

00:48:42.260 --> 00:48:45.260
But then once you'd done that, you had your piecework.

00:48:45.260 --> 00:48:49.260
But like I'm saying, you had to do so much before you could claim your piecework.

00:48:49.260 --> 00:48:53.260
And can you remember if you had pay rises regularly then?

00:48:53.260 --> 00:48:56.260
Well, we were putting in for them every year.

00:48:56.260 --> 00:48:59.260
If we didn't, we'd go out on strike.

00:48:59.260 --> 00:49:01.260
Yeah, we were.

00:49:01.260 --> 00:49:03.260
Were there strikes? Yes.

00:49:03.260 --> 00:49:06.260
What were they about usually?

00:49:06.260 --> 00:49:09.260
If it was too hot there, because you wouldn't work in the heat.

00:49:09.260 --> 00:49:13.260
And they wouldn't give you nothing because they used to give you salt tablets at one time.

00:49:13.260 --> 00:49:17.260
And if they didn't give you anything, we'd walk out.

00:49:17.260 --> 00:49:19.260
So everything would be on stop then?

00:49:19.260 --> 00:49:21.260
Everything would be on stop if it was too cold.

00:49:21.260 --> 00:49:24.260
So who would call you out? The shop steward?

00:49:24.260 --> 00:49:28.260
No, just more or less either the boys or whatever.

00:49:28.260 --> 00:49:30.260
But you'd go and see the shop steward.

00:49:30.260 --> 00:49:33.260
You'd tell him your point of view and he'd say,

00:49:33.260 --> 00:49:37.260
Well, we'll have to go. We'll have to see about it.

00:49:37.260 --> 00:49:40.260
So we'd all walk out, get the management down to see you,

00:49:40.260 --> 00:49:42.260
talk about it if they didn't like it,

00:49:42.260 --> 00:49:44.260
well, we'll see you tomorrow.

00:49:44.260 --> 00:49:45.260
And that's who it was.

00:49:45.260 --> 00:49:47.260
Do you think you had the power then?

00:49:47.260 --> 00:49:49.260
We did. We had the power.

00:49:49.260 --> 00:49:53.260
It was the workers had the say in them days, not like today.

00:49:53.260 --> 00:49:57.260
And I think a lot of it the youngsters have let go.

00:49:57.260 --> 00:50:01.260
Because the youngsters were too afraid to lose their jobs.

00:50:01.260 --> 00:50:05.260
Which is fair enough. There's no jobs to go to today, is there?

00:50:05.260 --> 00:50:06.260
No.

00:50:06.260 --> 00:50:12.260
But I feel sorry for them because they're letting the work rule them.

00:50:12.260 --> 00:50:15.260
But we didn't. We ruled the work.

00:50:15.260 --> 00:50:17.260
And we worked hard for it.

00:50:17.260 --> 00:50:20.260
So they were gaining as well as us.

00:50:20.260 --> 00:50:22.260
So it was pretty good.

00:50:27.260 --> 00:50:30.260
So how would you, when you first started there, you were very young.

00:50:30.260 --> 00:50:33.260
How did you spend your money? Did you give some at home?

00:50:33.260 --> 00:50:35.260
Oh, yes, I had to give some money at home.

00:50:35.260 --> 00:50:37.260
You didn't give your pay package to your mother though?

00:50:37.260 --> 00:50:40.260
Because some girls, I know, give the whole pay package in your pocket.

00:50:40.260 --> 00:50:42.260
No, no. I never did that and I never will.

00:50:42.260 --> 00:50:45.260
I wouldn't do it to my own man and I wouldn't do it to anybody.

00:50:45.260 --> 00:50:48.260
No, you'd tell him what you had and I'd give her so much a week.

00:50:48.260 --> 00:50:51.260
Well, I had to keep so much back for bus fare.

00:50:51.260 --> 00:50:55.260
And if I spent my bus fare like I told you, I had to walk very often.

00:50:55.260 --> 00:50:59.260
So that was my look out. I'd never ask my mother for a penny.

00:50:59.260 --> 00:51:01.260
I wouldn't ask her for any money back.

00:51:01.260 --> 00:51:03.260
Because she'd tell me where to go, I think.

00:51:03.260 --> 00:51:09.260
But if I didn't have my own bus fare, it was my fault and I'd have to be penalised.

00:51:09.260 --> 00:51:11.260
I'd get to work with my men.

00:51:11.260 --> 00:51:13.260
It was the penalit.

00:51:13.260 --> 00:51:16.260
But your social life at the time was around the factory more or less?

00:51:16.260 --> 00:51:17.260
Yes.

00:51:17.260 --> 00:51:24.260
So what type of thing, what type of events did they have on?

00:51:24.260 --> 00:51:26.260
Well, we'd go on trips.

00:51:26.260 --> 00:51:29.260
They'd organise trips. They were one of the girls.

00:51:29.260 --> 00:51:34.260
We'd organise a trip and we'd go out to Gosainan or anywhere like that.

00:51:34.260 --> 00:51:36.260
So the girls themselves would organise a trip?

00:51:36.260 --> 00:51:39.260
Organise a trip. Oh yes, they wouldn't do it for you.

00:51:39.260 --> 00:51:40.260
Oh, they wouldn't?

00:51:40.260 --> 00:51:41.260
Oh, God, no.

00:51:41.260 --> 00:51:44.260
They must have organised a Christmas party or something for you, did they?

00:51:44.260 --> 00:51:46.260
No, no. We used to do it yourself.

00:51:46.260 --> 00:51:47.260
All right.

00:51:47.260 --> 00:51:51.260
We used to take bulls into work. We'd aid it all year.

00:51:51.260 --> 00:51:54.260
And then we'd have a party then on the last day.

00:51:54.260 --> 00:51:56.260
We'd get the four men. We'd try and stop it, mind.

00:51:56.260 --> 00:51:59.260
But by the end of it, they joined in.

00:51:59.260 --> 00:52:02.260
We were having a party at nine o'clock in the morning.

00:52:02.260 --> 00:52:05.260
Oh, we'd have some fun. We did.

00:52:05.260 --> 00:52:07.260
Pardon me, we worked hard and played hard.

00:52:07.260 --> 00:52:11.260
Were there any perks for working in the factory?

00:52:11.260 --> 00:52:14.260
Yes, you'd get your silencers cheaper.

00:52:14.260 --> 00:52:16.260
You know, you could have things cheaper.

00:52:16.260 --> 00:52:18.260
You could get your cars cheaper.

00:52:18.260 --> 00:52:21.260
The trouble is we couldn't afford it.

00:52:21.260 --> 00:52:23.260
No.

00:52:23.260 --> 00:52:28.260
I say, you know, when I knew a tall was £300 and something,

00:52:28.260 --> 00:52:33.260
you know, that would be a lot for us to spend then.

00:52:33.260 --> 00:52:35.260
So we couldn't afford it.

00:52:35.260 --> 00:52:38.260
But I mean, it would be cheaper than buying it in the garage.

00:52:38.260 --> 00:52:44.260
I can't say about 25% cheaper, something like that.

00:52:44.260 --> 00:52:46.260
But still, you couldn't afford it.

00:52:46.260 --> 00:52:49.260
If I couldn't afford bus fare, I'm damn sure I couldn't afford a car.

00:52:49.260 --> 00:52:51.260
But why couldn't you afford bus fare then?

00:52:51.260 --> 00:52:53.260
Were you spending all your money?

00:52:53.260 --> 00:52:55.260
I spent my money on something else.

00:52:55.260 --> 00:52:56.260
Like what?

00:52:56.260 --> 00:52:58.260
Stockings.

00:52:58.260 --> 00:53:00.260
I thought you were it buying stockings.

00:53:00.260 --> 00:53:02.260
Because you couldn't afford them.

00:53:02.260 --> 00:53:04.260
You used to have your mother's after that.

00:53:04.260 --> 00:53:07.260
You know, so we had the things like that, you know.

00:53:07.260 --> 00:53:10.260
Cigarettes then when I smoked it.

00:53:10.260 --> 00:53:12.260
Did a lot of the girls smoke?

00:53:12.260 --> 00:53:14.260
Yes, most of them.

00:53:14.260 --> 00:53:16.260
Most of the girls smoked in them days.

00:53:16.260 --> 00:53:20.260
But what if you were gasping for a cigarette then?

00:53:20.260 --> 00:53:23.260
You couldn't just leave while you were working?

00:53:23.260 --> 00:53:25.260
Oh, you smoke on the job.

00:53:25.260 --> 00:53:26.260
Oh, right.

00:53:26.260 --> 00:53:28.260
Yes, you could smoke on the job then.

00:53:28.260 --> 00:53:30.260
You'd have a cigarette for that.

00:53:30.260 --> 00:53:32.260
You're lucky you didn't go up with that girl's hair then.

00:53:32.260 --> 00:53:34.260
Oh, no, we used to smoke on the factory then.

00:53:34.260 --> 00:53:36.260
There was nothing.

00:53:36.260 --> 00:53:37.260
And they didn't mind that?

00:53:37.260 --> 00:53:38.260
No.

00:53:38.260 --> 00:53:40.260
Well, I suppose it was benefiting them.

00:53:40.260 --> 00:53:42.260
Well, it's never been an issue.

00:53:42.260 --> 00:53:44.260
Because the foreman would walk around with a fag in his mouth.

00:53:44.260 --> 00:53:49.260
It's never been an issue in work until they're smoking him in.

00:53:49.260 --> 00:53:54.260
Do you think that the bosses were fair?

00:53:54.260 --> 00:53:57.260
Do you think they were good employers?

00:53:57.260 --> 00:53:59.260
Some of them were.

00:53:59.260 --> 00:54:02.260
I don't think.

00:54:02.260 --> 00:54:04.260
I liked Reed.

00:54:04.260 --> 00:54:06.260
Like I say, I liked one of the bosses.

00:54:06.260 --> 00:54:08.260
He was lovely.

00:54:08.260 --> 00:54:11.260
But I was cheeky to them as well, ma'am.

00:54:11.260 --> 00:54:14.260
I wouldn't let them get away with anything.

00:54:14.260 --> 00:54:16.260
But I think you're better off if you're cheeky.

00:54:16.260 --> 00:54:18.260
I'm better off if you're cheeky, aren't you?

00:54:18.260 --> 00:54:20.260
If you're a bit nervous of them, yes.

00:54:20.260 --> 00:54:22.260
Nervous of them, yes.

00:54:22.260 --> 00:54:24.260
Nervous of them, yes.

00:54:24.260 --> 00:54:26.260
No, no, I got on good with them.

00:54:26.260 --> 00:54:29.260
So you were talking about disputes earlier and problems and stuff.

00:54:29.260 --> 00:54:32.260
It was normally about the temperature, or was it about other things as well?

00:54:32.260 --> 00:54:36.260
Oh, no, about the work, about the work conditions.

00:54:36.260 --> 00:54:42.260
And you'd find out then that another company doing the same job as you were getting W.O. wages.

00:54:42.260 --> 00:54:45.260
And you'd find this out because it's something would come in a pallet.

00:54:45.260 --> 00:54:49.260
You'd read it, oh, look at this, same thing, same job.

00:54:49.260 --> 00:54:51.260
And then it was, you know.

00:54:51.260 --> 00:54:54.260
What type of thing would come in a pallet from the same company?

00:54:54.260 --> 00:55:01.260
Same company from, because we were working for companies that were in Longbridge.

00:55:01.260 --> 00:55:03.260
And was the other one, Oxford.

00:55:03.260 --> 00:55:09.260
And we'd get pallets for them and it would show somebody had put his payslip in there.

00:55:09.260 --> 00:55:12.260
You know, we'd find out how much they were earning.

00:55:12.260 --> 00:55:14.260
And the same company.

00:55:14.260 --> 00:55:16.260
So that's why we used to go up to the strike then.

00:55:16.260 --> 00:55:20.260
Then they used to try and tell us the cost of living was more up there.

00:55:20.260 --> 00:55:24.260
But it wasn't terrible to what we were paying.

00:55:24.260 --> 00:55:27.260
So then we'd go up to the strike, we'd make a bit more money.

00:55:27.260 --> 00:55:31.260
We'd get more holidays because at the time we weren't having much holidays.

00:55:31.260 --> 00:55:34.260
So that's what we used to fight for.

00:55:34.260 --> 00:55:38.260
For holidays, which they're letting go again today.

00:55:38.260 --> 00:55:41.260
How much holidays did you used to have?

00:55:41.260 --> 00:55:43.260
Christmas Day.

00:55:43.260 --> 00:55:45.260
That was your lot.

00:55:45.260 --> 00:55:47.260
And you'd have a fortnight in the summer.

00:55:47.260 --> 00:55:49.260
Shut down then, is it?

00:55:49.260 --> 00:55:51.260
Shut down.

00:55:51.260 --> 00:55:53.260
And that was your lot.

00:55:53.260 --> 00:55:55.260
I think you used to get a week in October sometimes.

00:55:55.260 --> 00:55:58.260
And then you started going into September.

00:55:58.260 --> 00:56:00.260
But that was your lot.

00:56:00.260 --> 00:56:03.260
You had no, and your bank holidays, of course your bank holidays.

00:56:03.260 --> 00:56:05.260
Which went so much then.

00:56:05.260 --> 00:56:10.260
How did the workers get on with the four men and the four women then?

00:56:10.260 --> 00:56:17.260
Once somebody had left, since somebody had become a four woman, would they get a bit up themselves then?

00:56:17.260 --> 00:56:19.260
Some of them would, yes.

00:56:19.260 --> 00:56:21.260
One has just left now.

00:56:21.260 --> 00:56:23.260
Yes, they would.

00:56:23.260 --> 00:56:26.260
Some of them would forget where they'd come from.

00:56:26.260 --> 00:56:29.260
You know, forget they'd been on the shop floor.

00:56:29.260 --> 00:56:34.260
Because it should make them a better four woman really, shouldn't it, if they know what the work is like.

00:56:34.260 --> 00:56:40.260
Yes, but no, some of them were quite, get on and do it type of thing, or I'll report you.

00:56:40.260 --> 00:56:44.260
So some of the girls didn't get on with them after.

00:56:44.260 --> 00:56:47.260
I got on with them all, I couldn't get a damn what they'd done.

00:56:47.260 --> 00:56:49.260
I mean, that's me.

00:56:49.260 --> 00:56:52.260
But some of them I know didn't get on with them, did they?

00:56:52.260 --> 00:56:54.260
You know.

00:56:54.260 --> 00:56:56.260
Yeah, it's a shame, isn't it?

00:56:56.260 --> 00:56:58.260
Yeah, it is a shame.

00:56:58.260 --> 00:57:00.260
Because it's good luck to them if they can get on and do it.

00:57:00.260 --> 00:57:02.260
But, you know, try and be fair with people.

00:57:02.260 --> 00:57:04.260
I know where you're from, I do.

00:57:04.260 --> 00:57:07.260
You've got to remember that their orders were coming from above as well.

00:57:07.260 --> 00:57:08.260
Yeah.

00:57:08.260 --> 00:57:10.260
Because like I'm saying, I didn't hit it at one point myself.

00:57:10.260 --> 00:57:11.260
Yeah.

00:57:11.260 --> 00:57:13.260
So my orders were coming from top.

00:57:13.260 --> 00:57:14.260
Yeah.

00:57:14.260 --> 00:57:17.260
And I was only giving what I had been told to tell them.

00:57:17.260 --> 00:57:18.260
Yeah.

00:57:18.260 --> 00:57:19.260
So.

00:57:22.260 --> 00:57:24.260
We've talked about accidents.

00:57:24.260 --> 00:57:25.260
Yeah.

00:57:25.260 --> 00:57:28.260
You were saying you had to pay for the gloves, but you've got the money back.

00:57:28.260 --> 00:57:30.260
Money back, yeah.

00:57:30.260 --> 00:57:33.260
Can you remember any of the rules and regulations?

00:57:33.260 --> 00:57:37.260
I know as far as health and safety wasn't as strong then.

00:57:37.260 --> 00:57:38.260
No.

00:57:38.260 --> 00:57:39.260
Can you remember any of the rules?

00:57:39.260 --> 00:57:41.260
You had to clock in and clock out.

00:57:41.260 --> 00:57:42.260
Oh, you had to clock in and clock out.

00:57:42.260 --> 00:57:43.260
Yeah.

00:57:43.260 --> 00:57:44.260
Was there anything else?

00:57:44.260 --> 00:57:46.260
You had to have a pass if you wanted to go out.

00:57:46.260 --> 00:57:48.260
You had passes, what they call passes.

00:57:48.260 --> 00:57:49.260
Yeah.

00:57:49.260 --> 00:57:51.260
Did you tend to stay there lunchtime then?

00:57:51.260 --> 00:57:53.260
Because you didn't have much time, did you?

00:57:53.260 --> 00:57:57.260
No, we used to get, no, we'd go, sometimes we'd go down to the pub, men.

00:57:57.260 --> 00:57:58.260
Yeah.

00:57:58.260 --> 00:58:05.260
Yeah, we'd go down to the pub because there was no such thing as drinking and so we'd have a glass of beer or whatever, lager.

00:58:05.260 --> 00:58:06.260
Yeah.

00:58:06.260 --> 00:58:09.260
And I'd come back then, be merry, I'd start up again.

00:58:09.260 --> 00:58:10.260
Fuck.

00:58:12.260 --> 00:58:15.260
Oh no, it was, oh, pretty easy going.

00:58:15.260 --> 00:58:16.260
Yeah.

00:58:16.260 --> 00:58:22.260
Get caught in the Christmas then and I'd have to jump over the fence to get back in, you know, things like that.

00:58:22.260 --> 00:58:23.260
Yeah.

00:58:23.260 --> 00:58:25.260
But I mean, nothing was in.

00:58:25.260 --> 00:58:31.260
How would you describe the humour in the factory then, you know, sense of humour and leg pulling?

00:58:31.260 --> 00:58:34.260
Oh, good punter, good punter.

00:58:34.260 --> 00:58:40.260
We did have some good, some couldn't take it, men.

00:58:40.260 --> 00:58:43.260
You know, you'd have some crying and we'll get on with it.

00:58:43.260 --> 00:58:46.260
Would they be the younger ones or what, or just?

00:58:46.260 --> 00:58:48.260
No, no.

00:58:49.260 --> 00:58:50.260
I don't know, I think it was a mixture.

00:58:50.260 --> 00:58:54.260
What type of leg pulling would there be, playing practical jokes?

00:58:54.260 --> 00:58:57.260
Jokes, oh yeah, practical jokes, yeah.

00:58:57.260 --> 00:58:58.260
They do that.

00:58:58.260 --> 00:59:03.260
Because somebody welded my pliers to the table.

00:59:03.260 --> 00:59:06.260
I went to get my pliers, I thought that was wrong, yeah.

00:59:06.260 --> 00:59:07.260
You know, things like that.

00:59:07.260 --> 00:59:09.260
They were wicked when she was working.

00:59:09.260 --> 00:59:11.260
Yeah, they were wicked when I was working, oh.

00:59:11.260 --> 00:59:12.260
Yeah.

00:59:12.260 --> 00:59:14.260
We did have some fun.

00:59:14.260 --> 00:59:15.260
Yeah.

00:59:15.260 --> 00:59:16.260
So what type of person do you want to take?

00:59:16.260 --> 00:59:17.260
They put you on a conveyor then.

00:59:17.260 --> 00:59:18.260
Oh.

00:59:18.260 --> 00:59:23.260
Or like onesy, they put my friend then on a bloody fountain, water fountain, just sit.

00:59:23.260 --> 00:59:24.260
Shut up.

00:59:24.260 --> 00:59:26.260
Shove me in the cage.

00:59:26.260 --> 00:59:29.260
I'd tell you to go to the toilet, throw me a bucket over.

00:59:29.260 --> 00:59:30.260
You know, things like that.

00:59:30.260 --> 00:59:32.260
We used to have good banter.

00:59:32.260 --> 00:59:33.260
Really good.

00:59:33.260 --> 00:59:35.260
So, major day.

00:59:35.260 --> 00:59:37.260
And we still had the workouts.

00:59:37.260 --> 00:59:38.260
Yeah.

00:59:38.260 --> 00:59:41.260
You were talking earlier about the factory being too hot.

00:59:41.260 --> 00:59:43.260
Did it get too cold in the winter as well?

00:59:43.260 --> 00:59:45.260
Yes, it got too cold in the winter.

00:59:45.260 --> 00:59:46.260
Yeah.

00:59:46.260 --> 00:59:47.260
Very cold.

00:59:47.260 --> 00:59:51.260
Because they changed the heating, I think, four times when I worked there.

00:59:51.260 --> 00:59:52.260
Oh, right.

00:59:52.260 --> 00:59:55.260
They had like gas fires up on the ceiling.

00:59:55.260 --> 00:59:58.260
Then they put in this central heating thing that didn't work.

00:59:58.260 --> 01:00:00.260
Then they'd have to change it.

01:00:00.260 --> 01:00:03.260
So I think they were spending money hand over face doing things like that.

01:00:03.260 --> 01:00:04.260
Yeah.

01:00:04.260 --> 01:00:05.260
And nothing worked really?

01:00:05.260 --> 01:00:06.260
Nothing worked, no.

01:00:06.260 --> 01:00:08.260
It was basically like a big shed then, was it?

01:00:08.260 --> 01:00:09.260
Yeah, of course it was, yeah.

01:00:09.260 --> 01:00:10.260
Yeah.

01:00:10.260 --> 01:00:14.260
What were the facilities like then, like the canteen and the toilets and everything?

01:00:14.260 --> 01:00:16.260
Well, we didn't have a canteen when we started there.

01:00:16.260 --> 01:00:17.260
Oh, didn't you?

01:00:17.260 --> 01:00:18.260
No, no.

01:00:18.260 --> 01:00:21.260
We used to sit on little ammunition boxes.

01:00:21.260 --> 01:00:24.260
You kept your overall in there, your shield in there and your tools.

01:00:24.260 --> 01:00:26.260
And that was your little ammunition box.

01:00:26.260 --> 01:00:27.260
Yeah.

01:00:27.260 --> 01:00:29.260
Because you had no lockers and nothing.

01:00:29.260 --> 01:00:32.260
And then that was your sit down then for your breaks.

01:00:32.260 --> 01:00:34.260
Just have your thing.

01:00:34.260 --> 01:00:35.260
There was a canteen, mine.

01:00:35.260 --> 01:00:36.260
Yeah.

01:00:36.260 --> 01:00:38.260
They had a canteen, but that was outside the factory.

01:00:38.260 --> 01:00:41.260
The time you'd walked up there, your afternoon was gone.

01:00:41.260 --> 01:00:42.260
Yeah.

01:00:42.260 --> 01:00:43.260
So what did you do then?

01:00:43.260 --> 01:00:44.260
Did you take apart lunch or something?

01:00:44.260 --> 01:00:46.260
Sandwiches or something you'd take.

01:00:46.260 --> 01:00:47.260
Yeah.

01:00:47.260 --> 01:00:49.260
Did they play music or something for you?

01:00:49.260 --> 01:00:51.260
They did at one time.

01:00:51.260 --> 01:00:55.260
They did start, then they stopped and then they started back then.

01:00:55.260 --> 01:00:59.260
When they first started there, you were having music for two hours a day.

01:00:59.260 --> 01:01:00.260
Yeah.

01:01:00.260 --> 01:01:01.260
What, the radio then?

01:01:01.260 --> 01:01:03.260
The radio was on throughout the factory, you know.

01:01:03.260 --> 01:01:07.260
But then they stopped it, then they brought it back then at one time, didn't they?

01:01:07.260 --> 01:01:09.260
Why did they stop it then?

01:01:09.260 --> 01:01:12.260
Oh, because it was interfering, it was supposed to be with your work.

01:01:12.260 --> 01:01:13.260
Oh.

01:01:13.260 --> 01:01:15.260
Because the rules started changing.

01:01:16.260 --> 01:01:17.260
In what way?

01:01:17.260 --> 01:01:18.260
In what way?

01:01:18.260 --> 01:01:21.260
They started getting bitchy about things, you know.

01:01:21.260 --> 01:01:22.260
After they'd been passed.

01:01:22.260 --> 01:01:25.260
Yes, certain things and they'd start...

01:01:26.260 --> 01:01:28.260
Why is that then? To show the boss was?

01:01:28.260 --> 01:01:30.260
To show the boss was, yes.

01:01:31.260 --> 01:01:34.260
I'm boss, you do as I told, as you're told.

01:01:34.260 --> 01:01:37.260
Well, I used to tell them, if you can do this job, I'll do it after you.

01:01:37.260 --> 01:01:38.260
Yeah.

01:01:38.260 --> 01:01:41.260
But no, no, I couldn't do that, never done the job.

01:01:41.260 --> 01:01:43.260
So who are you to tell me how to do it then?

01:01:43.260 --> 01:01:44.260
You know.

01:01:44.260 --> 01:01:50.260
Did things change then when it stopped being piecework and you had a flat rate then, is it?

01:01:51.260 --> 01:01:56.260
Well, some found it better, but others found it hard. Didn't they?

01:01:57.260 --> 01:01:59.260
You can't say why.

01:01:59.260 --> 01:02:00.260
Yeah.

01:02:00.260 --> 01:02:01.260
Because they were cheating.

01:02:01.260 --> 01:02:02.260
Because they were flogging.

01:02:03.260 --> 01:02:05.260
A lot of them used to flog at one time.

01:02:05.260 --> 01:02:06.260
Say they didn't.

01:02:07.260 --> 01:02:12.260
But you couldn't blame them then because they were doing the work and it was hard work at that time.

01:02:12.260 --> 01:02:16.260
So say they'd done 50, they'd book in 75.

01:02:16.260 --> 01:02:17.260
Yeah.

01:02:17.260 --> 01:02:19.260
Couldn't they assess that?

01:02:19.260 --> 01:02:21.260
No, listen, I'm going to be in court over this now.

01:02:21.260 --> 01:02:22.260
No, you're not.

01:02:22.260 --> 01:02:24.260
They were bloody kicking all the day.

01:02:24.260 --> 01:02:25.260
Right, yeah.

01:02:26.260 --> 01:02:28.260
That's what they used to do with it.

01:02:29.260 --> 01:02:41.260
And then when the other parts of the factory then were the goody-goody years, they found it harder then because easier because they had already, you know, they weren't doing so much flogging.

01:02:42.260 --> 01:02:43.260
As they call it.

01:02:43.260 --> 01:02:46.260
Very vulnerable. Can you hear me now if I say it?

01:02:46.260 --> 01:02:47.260
Yeah.

01:02:47.260 --> 01:02:49.260
I can't, I bet if I don't say it.

01:02:49.260 --> 01:02:50.260
No, yeah.

01:02:51.260 --> 01:02:53.260
No, you went by out on the seats then.

01:02:53.260 --> 01:02:58.260
Yeah, very by out on the seats. That's what I was saying, we were very humanised down there.

01:02:58.260 --> 01:02:59.260
Oh, right, on the seats.

01:02:59.260 --> 01:03:00.260
On the seats. I'm not the pressure.

01:03:00.260 --> 01:03:04.260
How did you have by out when we went weekly rates?

01:03:04.260 --> 01:03:09.260
Yeah, with, like my husband, we was packing glass of wool.

01:03:09.260 --> 01:03:10.260
Yeah.

01:03:10.260 --> 01:03:12.260
And it was a dangerous job because.

01:03:12.260 --> 01:03:13.260
Oh, that gets into your hands.

01:03:13.260 --> 01:03:15.260
It goes up into your lungs and everything.

01:03:15.260 --> 01:03:16.260
Yeah, yeah.

01:03:16.260 --> 01:03:25.260
Well, I mean, I was working with it because I had to take the work off them to do it and I was welding, which it does more thing for me because I was covered in it.

01:03:25.260 --> 01:03:32.260
So they sold out their piece of work. They sold out their rates. Well, they had a couple of hundred pound for it.

01:03:32.260 --> 01:03:33.260
Yeah.

01:03:33.260 --> 01:03:37.260
But I was still, well, I had to do it, you know what I mean?

01:03:38.260 --> 01:03:41.260
And that's how we do so one little things, little pitchy things.

01:03:41.260 --> 01:03:42.260
Yeah.

01:03:44.260 --> 01:03:49.260
But shouldn't a manager have been able to sort that out or weren't they aware of little things?

01:03:49.260 --> 01:03:51.260
They had to go through the union.

01:03:51.260 --> 01:03:52.260
Oh, right.

01:03:52.260 --> 01:03:56.260
Because if anything like that happened, the union would be the middleman.

01:03:56.260 --> 01:03:57.260
Yeah.

01:03:57.260 --> 01:04:01.260
Were the union in a difficult position then, do you think, sometimes?

01:04:01.260 --> 01:04:02.260
No, no.

01:04:02.260 --> 01:04:03.260
No?

01:04:03.260 --> 01:04:11.260
The union were the bosses at that time because, I mean, it was, the union was strong, very strong at that time.

01:04:11.260 --> 01:04:12.260
Yeah.

01:04:12.260 --> 01:04:16.260
So I think it was the union that told the management and told you, me.

01:04:16.260 --> 01:04:19.260
But do you think they'll damage things at all?

01:04:19.260 --> 01:04:20.260
No.

01:04:20.260 --> 01:04:21.260
No.

01:04:21.260 --> 01:04:22.260
No.

01:04:22.260 --> 01:04:29.260
Because people today tend to say that unions were too strong back then. Would you disagree with that?

01:04:29.260 --> 01:04:35.260
No, not really. No, because you, today you haven't got a union.

01:04:35.260 --> 01:04:36.260
No.

01:04:36.260 --> 01:04:43.260
You haven't got a union today because, like I said, I went on the union and you were told, don't make too much fuss.

01:04:43.260 --> 01:04:48.260
You know, you've got to, which I didn't want to do because, I mean, like I told you, I'm very unionized.

01:04:48.260 --> 01:04:49.260
Yeah.

01:04:49.260 --> 01:04:54.260
I was very militant at that time then. But so I couldn't.

01:04:54.260 --> 01:04:58.260
Why did you feel like that then? Did you feel that people were taking for granted?

01:04:58.260 --> 01:04:59.260
I thought that.

01:04:59.260 --> 01:05:00.260
Taking advantage.

01:05:00.260 --> 01:05:03.260
Taking advantage of other people. And I don't like that.

01:05:03.260 --> 01:05:07.260
So where has that come from in you then, do you think?

01:05:07.260 --> 01:05:10.260
I don't know, whether it's come from my own background.

01:05:10.260 --> 01:05:11.260
Yeah.

01:05:11.260 --> 01:05:17.260
I don't know. Because my father wasn't working, I think.

01:05:17.260 --> 01:05:22.260
Maybe because I was taking the mick out of something at one time.

01:05:22.260 --> 01:05:26.260
Your father's not working, you can't have this. Let that will have, let he will have it.

01:05:26.260 --> 01:05:27.260
Yeah.

01:05:27.260 --> 01:05:28.260
You know.

01:05:28.260 --> 01:05:29.260
Yeah.

01:05:29.260 --> 01:05:30.260
Have I made you stronger then?

01:05:30.260 --> 01:05:31.260
I think so.

01:05:31.260 --> 01:05:32.260
Yeah.

01:05:32.260 --> 01:05:37.260
Eddie. Oh, again I can never drop it in the court, my throat is hoarse now.

01:05:37.260 --> 01:05:38.260
We nearly finished.

01:05:38.260 --> 01:05:39.260
You'll have to take that off.

01:05:39.260 --> 01:05:40.260
Yeah, I'll get that.

01:05:40.260 --> 01:05:41.260
Haven't you got any in there?

01:05:41.260 --> 01:05:44.260
Yes, I've got some in there.

01:05:44.260 --> 01:05:49.260
I'll just ask you a bit now. You said, you know, when you went there, you met your husband there.

01:05:49.260 --> 01:05:54.260
So did that work then with both of you being and working in the same place and knowing the same people?

01:05:54.260 --> 01:05:55.260
Do you think that made you stronger?

01:05:55.260 --> 01:05:58.260
Oh yes, because we used to go out with couples.

01:05:58.260 --> 01:05:59.260
Yeah.

01:05:59.260 --> 01:06:05.260
You know, they just, the couples that I'd met there.

01:06:05.260 --> 01:06:06.260
Yeah.

01:06:06.260 --> 01:06:10.260
Well, we used to go out with them, like if you had a car, you'd go to them couple.

