Yeah.

01:06:11.260 --> 01:06:16.260
And they'd say, welcome now to this. And we all used to go out to the Marshmortar club in the gang.

01:06:16.260 --> 01:06:17.260
Yeah.

01:06:17.260 --> 01:06:20.260
And we'd just go out. You'd fall out now and again with some of them of mine.

01:06:20.260 --> 01:06:21.260
Yeah.

01:06:21.260 --> 01:06:22.260
Well, you do when you're close, don't you?

01:06:22.260 --> 01:06:24.260
But it wouldn't be for long, you know, you could make up.

01:06:24.260 --> 01:06:25.260
Yeah.

01:06:25.260 --> 01:06:29.260
You wouldn't stay angry with somebody. Because I can't, I've got to.

01:06:29.260 --> 01:06:30.260
Make up.

01:06:30.260 --> 01:06:32.260
Make up. Either you like me or you don't like me.

01:06:32.260 --> 01:06:36.260
Like I say, I make a good friend, but I'm a horrible enemy.

01:06:36.260 --> 01:06:37.260
So don't make an enemy of me.

01:06:37.260 --> 01:06:38.260
Scared of me now?

01:06:38.260 --> 01:06:39.260
Yeah.

01:06:39.260 --> 01:06:43.260
But that's the way I am, Gynedd, isn't it? You either make a friend of me or don't.

01:06:43.260 --> 01:06:44.260
Yeah.

01:06:45.260 --> 01:06:49.260
Was there much quarrelling there then? Because working side by side with people.

01:06:49.260 --> 01:06:51.260
Oh, Christ, aye. Oh, yes, you used to have quarrels.

01:06:51.260 --> 01:06:52.260
Yeah.

01:06:52.260 --> 01:06:53.260
What about?

01:06:53.260 --> 01:06:54.260
About the work.

01:06:54.260 --> 01:06:55.260
About the work.

01:06:55.260 --> 01:06:56.260
About the work.

01:06:56.260 --> 01:07:01.260
About people doing, oh, you're doing that overtime? Overtime was a big thing there.

01:07:01.260 --> 01:07:02.260
Yeah.

01:07:02.260 --> 01:07:04.260
What, that some people have been given a chance?

01:07:04.260 --> 01:07:06.260
A chance to get more overtime than others.

01:07:06.260 --> 01:07:13.260
But did some people exploit their power a bit then? Because if you've got overtime to give, right, you've got power then, haven't you?

01:07:13.260 --> 01:07:14.260
Yeah, of course you have.

01:07:14.260 --> 01:07:15.260
Yeah.

01:07:15.260 --> 01:07:25.260
So I think they used to. Because at one time it was just, you were told, well, you're working on tonight, well, you do it, you know, if you could.

01:07:25.260 --> 01:07:26.260
Yeah.

01:07:26.260 --> 01:07:35.260
But if you couldn't then, and they'd make a fuss about it, it was either do it or we'll give it to somebody else for the rest of the week then.

01:07:35.260 --> 01:07:36.260
Oh, like.

01:07:36.260 --> 01:07:37.260
You know.

01:07:37.260 --> 01:07:38.260
Yeah.

01:07:38.260 --> 01:07:40.260
So you used to try and take it if you could take it.

01:07:40.260 --> 01:07:42.260
How many days a week did you work?

01:07:42.260 --> 01:07:47.260
Five, but you used to get Saturday in. There was no Sundays at winter, was there?

01:07:47.260 --> 01:07:48.260
No, later on.

01:07:48.260 --> 01:07:50.260
No, later on Sundays came.

01:07:50.260 --> 01:07:54.260
Yeah. And how many breaks would you have then?

01:07:54.260 --> 01:08:06.260
Oh, when I first started there. You used to get your breakfast and your dinner. I don't think you had a break after that because, like I say, you could smoke, have a cup of tea on the job.

01:08:06.260 --> 01:08:08.260
Yeah. Did they bring a drill? Did they bring the teemachiner?

01:08:08.260 --> 01:08:09.260
No, you had a teemachiner.

01:08:09.260 --> 01:08:10.260
Oh, right.

01:08:10.260 --> 01:08:12.260
Yeah, when they first brought the teemachiner in.

01:08:12.260 --> 01:08:13.260
Yeah.

01:08:13.260 --> 01:08:21.260
We've talked about holidays. Did you ever go on holiday with people from work?

01:08:21.260 --> 01:08:23.260
Yes, we still do.

01:08:23.260 --> 01:08:24.260
Oh, do you?

01:08:24.260 --> 01:08:27.260
Yes. We still do it. Yes, we've done it for years.

01:08:27.260 --> 01:08:28.260
Where did you go?

01:08:28.260 --> 01:08:31.260
But, Glens, we went in the first, starting off.

01:08:31.260 --> 01:08:32.260
Yeah.

01:08:32.260 --> 01:08:34.260
Then we went to Spain.

01:08:34.260 --> 01:08:38.260
You've come to get on well with people to work and go on holidays with.

01:08:38.260 --> 01:08:46.260
Go on holidays with, yeah. But I tell you what, I'm still friends with mine now after some of them 38 years, 40 years.

01:08:46.260 --> 01:08:49.260
So, you understand each other then.

01:08:49.260 --> 01:08:51.260
Yeah. Well, you're more like family.

01:08:51.260 --> 01:08:52.260
Yeah.

01:08:52.260 --> 01:08:55.260
You're more like family than your own family. Do you get me?

01:08:55.260 --> 01:08:56.260
Yeah.

01:08:58.260 --> 01:09:03.260
We talked a bit about Christmas at the factory. Before, did people decorate and stuff?

01:09:03.260 --> 01:09:10.260
Oh, yes. Oh, yes. We had a good atmosphere. We used to decorate. All the machines had to stop because of health and safety.

01:09:10.260 --> 01:09:11.260
Wow.

01:09:11.260 --> 01:09:20.260
But we used to do everything. We used to put little bells and things on and streamers up. We used to do everything, didn't we?

01:09:20.260 --> 01:09:21.260
So, the last...

01:09:21.260 --> 01:09:22.260
The cop, the cop.

01:09:22.260 --> 01:09:26.260
But it was there, right? Make our own decorations.

01:09:27.260 --> 01:09:31.260
The last working day before Christmas was the best one then, was it?

01:09:31.260 --> 01:09:34.260
Oh, yes. Well, that was your only day off.

01:09:34.260 --> 01:09:35.260
Yeah.

01:09:35.260 --> 01:09:37.260
Christmas was your only day off.

01:09:37.260 --> 01:09:40.260
So, what time would work stop on that day?

01:09:40.260 --> 01:09:41.260
Well, you wouldn't start.

01:09:41.260 --> 01:09:42.260
Oh.

01:09:44.260 --> 01:09:53.260
So, that's how we had an extra day really because you used to go in by seven, by, well, upper seven, I think it was. Yeah, seven at once. I can remember it as seven.

01:09:54.260 --> 01:10:01.260
But then I think from upper seven, then you'd work until about upper eight and then you'd start drinking then at nine o'clock.

01:10:02.260 --> 01:10:11.260
We'd open the bars then. They used to take chickens in and all the boys did. We'd have a party and then the foreman would come round, you can't do this, you can't do this. Give us a drink.

01:10:12.260 --> 01:10:14.260
You know, that's how they were. It was brilliant.

01:10:14.260 --> 01:10:15.260
Yeah.

01:10:16.260 --> 01:10:18.260
So, targets didn't matter or matter, did they?

01:10:18.260 --> 01:10:20.260
No, you'd already done your work for it anyway.

01:10:20.260 --> 01:10:21.260
Oh, right.

01:10:21.260 --> 01:10:31.260
See, that's what I'm saying. You used to book in. Now, say you'd done 400 the day before. 200 was for that day and 200 was for Christmas Eve.

01:10:31.260 --> 01:10:32.260
Yeah.

01:10:32.260 --> 01:10:33.260
And you used to book it in then.

01:10:33.260 --> 01:10:34.260
Yeah.

01:10:34.260 --> 01:10:36.260
So, according to them, you'd still done your work.

01:10:36.260 --> 01:10:42.260
Can you tell me a bit more about the social activities in the club? Because you had like a club house then, didn't you?

01:10:42.260 --> 01:10:43.260
Yeah.

01:10:43.260 --> 01:10:46.260
Well, it was in the canteen when I first started then. Then it went to the club.

01:10:46.260 --> 01:10:47.260
Yeah.

01:10:47.260 --> 01:10:50.260
But in the canteen, we used to have our dances and things.

01:10:50.260 --> 01:10:53.260
So, what type of thing? Do you have bands and stuff or...?

01:10:54.260 --> 01:11:01.260
Yes, I think we did have a band there a few times. And then it was more like records, what do you call them?

01:11:01.260 --> 01:11:02.260
Yeah, like a disco.

01:11:02.260 --> 01:11:04.260
Disco, but it wasn't disco then, was it?

01:11:04.260 --> 01:11:05.260
Yeah.

01:11:05.260 --> 01:11:08.260
A man and a record just doing...

01:11:09.260 --> 01:11:12.260
So, at Christmas time, was there a children's Christmas party there?

01:11:12.260 --> 01:11:14.260
No, we used to have a pantomime for them.

01:11:14.260 --> 01:11:15.260
Oh, did you?

01:11:15.260 --> 01:11:17.260
Yeah, we used to have a pantomime.

01:11:20.260 --> 01:11:23.260
I think it was in the January, I think they used to do it.

01:11:23.260 --> 01:11:25.260
Oh, they used to take them to the pantomime, you say?

01:11:25.260 --> 01:11:28.260
Well, give you tickets to take them. You used to take them.

01:11:28.260 --> 01:11:33.260
Do you have tickets to take them to...? And the old age used to get something out of them.

01:11:33.260 --> 01:11:35.260
Now they don't have nothing.

01:11:35.260 --> 01:11:39.260
But, girl, nobody gets anything out of them now.

01:11:39.260 --> 01:11:41.260
That's how bad it's gone.

01:11:41.260 --> 01:11:44.260
So, who used to go to the club then? Couples or...?

01:11:44.260 --> 01:11:46.260
Singles. Singles.

01:11:46.260 --> 01:11:49.260
That's a good way to get to know people who aren't on your section.

01:11:49.260 --> 01:11:51.260
Yes, I do see you're carrying on just now.

01:11:52.260 --> 01:11:55.260
That's a good way to get to know people who aren't on your section.

01:11:55.260 --> 01:11:56.260
Section, yeah.

01:11:56.260 --> 01:11:59.260
But what if you were on a section and you were stuck with certain people?

01:11:59.260 --> 01:12:02.260
Because you can get on bugger sometimes, can't you?

01:12:02.260 --> 01:12:05.260
Oh, yes. If you didn't like them, you'd have to...

01:12:05.260 --> 01:12:06.260
Lump it?

01:12:06.260 --> 01:12:07.260
Lump it.

01:12:07.260 --> 01:12:11.260
But, like I'm saying, you couldn't hear them talking anyway unless you looked at them.

01:12:11.260 --> 01:12:14.260
So, I mean, you'd say, no, then, if you didn't, what you got to do?

01:12:14.260 --> 01:12:16.260
And you weren't being ignorant then.

01:12:16.260 --> 01:12:18.260
So, you'd be wading, they'd be talking.

01:12:19.260 --> 01:12:21.260
And you'd think, oh, well, they can't hear me anyway.

01:12:21.260 --> 01:12:23.260
And I can't hear them.

01:12:25.260 --> 01:12:28.260
We're just summing up now. We're nearly finished, aren't we?

01:12:28.260 --> 01:12:31.260
Were there any sports teams there?

01:12:31.260 --> 01:12:35.260
Yes, you had shooting. I was a member of a shooting club there.

01:12:36.260 --> 01:12:40.260
I used to do it down in the Tiers place, down in Llellu.

01:12:40.260 --> 01:12:43.260
There was darts there, I done darts.

01:12:43.260 --> 01:12:46.260
We had knockouts. It's a knockout.

01:12:46.260 --> 01:12:48.260
So, where would that be held?

01:12:48.260 --> 01:12:51.260
It's a knockout, it was in the fields in Denham Hall.

01:12:51.260 --> 01:12:53.260
Oh, right, yes.

01:12:53.260 --> 01:12:56.260
Well, they had pageants there. I never went to one of them, though.

01:12:56.260 --> 01:12:57.260
Booty pageants.

01:12:57.260 --> 01:12:58.260
Oh, did they?

01:12:58.260 --> 01:12:59.260
Yes.

01:12:59.260 --> 01:13:00.260
Gosh.

01:13:00.260 --> 01:13:02.260
Well, they used to do a bit of everything then.

01:13:02.260 --> 01:13:05.260
So, there was a Miss Morris Motors, a Miss Lady, I remember.

01:13:05.260 --> 01:13:06.260
Yes, yes.

01:13:06.260 --> 01:13:09.260
Because, what do you call it? Just one, wasn't she?

01:13:09.260 --> 01:13:10.260
Elaine.

01:13:10.260 --> 01:13:13.260
Elaine was an attendant for somebody.

01:13:13.260 --> 01:13:14.260
It was a big thing.

01:13:14.260 --> 01:13:17.260
I think that was a big thing before I started, even.

01:13:17.260 --> 01:13:18.260
Yes.

01:13:18.260 --> 01:13:24.260
They used to have Miss Llinellu and Miss Morris Motors in the Llinellu carnival.

01:13:24.260 --> 01:13:25.260
Yes.

01:13:25.260 --> 01:13:28.260
They used to have durores, the maintenance was a durores.

01:13:28.260 --> 01:13:31.260
We used to do Christmas lorries. Well, they'd done them, it's been recently, mine.

01:13:31.260 --> 01:13:32.260
Yes.

01:13:32.260 --> 01:13:33.260
Carnival lorries, yes.

01:13:33.260 --> 01:13:34.260
Oh, right.

01:13:34.260 --> 01:13:37.260
Well, they used to be very social at one time.

01:13:37.260 --> 01:13:38.260
Yes.

01:13:38.260 --> 01:13:41.260
But I think it's going down, I don't think they've got anything now.

01:13:41.260 --> 01:13:43.260
Oh, so shame, isn't it?

01:13:43.260 --> 01:13:44.260
Yes.

01:13:44.260 --> 01:13:47.260
Well, even the youngsters don't come to the club with us, he says.

01:13:47.260 --> 01:13:50.260
Where do they go then? I don't think they go out as much.

01:13:50.260 --> 01:13:51.260
No, they don't, no.

01:13:51.260 --> 01:13:56.260
So, did you enjoy working at the factory?

01:13:56.260 --> 01:14:01.260
Yes, I did. I did enjoy it. I enjoyed the company.

01:14:01.260 --> 01:14:05.260
The work was heavy, like I say, but you got on and done it.

01:14:06.260 --> 01:14:10.260
And certain jobs I did enjoy, but when I finished up I was doing heavy work.

01:14:10.260 --> 01:14:16.260
I was doing big gradiators, so I think if I hadn't finished it would have finished me.

01:14:16.260 --> 01:14:22.260
Can you just go over your dates with me again? You started when you were 17, didn't you?

01:14:22.260 --> 01:14:24.260
Yes, 1967.

01:14:24.260 --> 01:14:28.260
And you worked then until you were pregnant with the first one?

01:14:28.260 --> 01:14:30.260
Yes, only one I had.

01:14:30.260 --> 01:14:32.260
1971.

01:14:32.260 --> 01:14:38.260
I went back in 1972, 1973 in between, because Christopher was a year and a bit.

01:14:38.260 --> 01:14:39.260
Was that part time then?

01:14:39.260 --> 01:14:41.260
Part time I'd done for five years.

01:14:41.260 --> 01:14:43.260
Then I went full time.

01:14:43.260 --> 01:14:46.260
Then they made us redundant.

01:14:46.260 --> 01:14:54.260
Then I went back full time then and I worked full time for five years as a temp.

01:14:54.260 --> 01:14:57.260
Oh, right, it was a temporary contract.

01:14:57.260 --> 01:15:01.260
Yes, that's why I was fighting against it and I fought against it.

01:15:01.260 --> 01:15:04.260
I think that's how they kept me so long.

01:15:04.260 --> 01:15:07.260
So I worked for five years, then I went on full time then.

01:15:07.260 --> 01:15:13.260
How long were the contracts then? If it was a temporary contract, did they just keep on renewing the same one?

01:15:13.260 --> 01:15:15.260
There was no such thing as time on it.

01:15:15.260 --> 01:15:21.260
Now there is, men. They've got a year, I think it is a year's contract now.

01:15:21.260 --> 01:15:23.260
I'm not sure what it is now.

01:15:23.260 --> 01:15:27.260
You got it done when you were two years in and you fought with it.

01:15:27.260 --> 01:15:30.260
You can't plan anything unless you know how long you've got a job.

01:15:30.260 --> 01:15:34.260
They'd finish you off a week before the two years and then they'd do another two years.

01:15:34.260 --> 01:15:37.260
Yes, and then they'd start you back a week after, or the day after.

01:15:37.260 --> 01:15:41.260
Very unfair like that, they were.

01:15:41.260 --> 01:15:46.260
If they didn't like your face, like I say, I was two chops here, and they didn't like my face.

01:15:46.260 --> 01:15:48.260
But they kept on having you back, they must have liked you.

01:15:48.260 --> 01:15:52.260
Yes, because of the work. They knew that I knew the work.

01:15:52.260 --> 01:15:55.260
Because I started jobs there and I finished them.

01:15:55.260 --> 01:16:03.260
They'd call me and say, I was doing the Princess card at one time, which was a very heavy seat.

01:16:03.260 --> 01:16:08.260
Started it off, they went to finish it up then because they were sending it to another company.

01:16:08.260 --> 01:16:15.260
Will you come and finish them for me? Sucker be, I used to go. That type of thing, you know.

01:16:15.260 --> 01:16:18.260
So when did you finish eventually then?

01:16:18.260 --> 01:16:21.260
2006.

01:16:21.260 --> 01:16:24.260
So how did you feel about?

01:16:24.260 --> 01:16:27.260
They had an accident before I finished.

01:16:27.260 --> 01:16:34.260
I slipped, I hurt my leg, I was taken to hospital, carried out on a stretcher.

01:16:34.260 --> 01:16:37.260
Never knew I'd be doing that though.

01:16:37.260 --> 01:16:43.260
That's how I finished then, and I had my redundancy, which they weren't willing to give me.

01:16:43.260 --> 01:16:45.260
But I had my redundancy then.

01:16:45.260 --> 01:16:47.260
Why weren't they willing? Because you'd been on a temporary contract.

01:16:47.260 --> 01:16:52.260
No, no, because I was full time this time. I'd done 20 years full time then.

01:16:52.260 --> 01:16:58.260
So they were afraid not to give it to me because I told them I'd take them to court.

01:16:58.260 --> 01:17:05.260
But they couldn't stop it anyway because I mean I'd put in for it to do something, you know.

01:17:05.260 --> 01:17:07.260
I'm going to be young for this.

01:17:07.260 --> 01:17:09.260
No, you're not.

01:17:09.260 --> 01:17:12.260
No, you're saying that, oh no, my voice is bad.

01:17:12.260 --> 01:17:14.260
It doesn't matter.

01:17:14.260 --> 01:17:16.260
It's not what you're saying.

01:17:16.260 --> 01:17:18.260
No, it's not like you're saying.

01:17:18.260 --> 01:17:23.260
There's more things happen to Yvonne than me there because I was staying in the same place.

01:17:23.260 --> 01:17:24.260
Very boring.

01:17:24.260 --> 01:17:27.260
Only two jobs I ever went on there.

01:17:27.260 --> 01:17:33.260
So you finished, was it because of your leg or were you ready to go anyway?

01:17:33.260 --> 01:17:37.260
No, no, I was going to finish anyway. I'd put in for my redundancy.

01:17:37.260 --> 01:17:40.260
I'd only put in to see because everybody was finishing.

01:17:40.260 --> 01:17:43.260
But when I fell I'd put the tin lid on it.

01:17:43.260 --> 01:17:46.260
I thought I couldn't work after that anyway.

01:17:46.260 --> 01:17:47.260
No.

01:17:47.260 --> 01:17:48.260
Because I did have a…

01:17:48.260 --> 01:17:50.260
About two months before I finished.

01:17:50.260 --> 01:17:53.260
Yeah, because I had a big bang.

01:17:56.260 --> 01:18:05.260
What struck me talking to a lot of women now is that they have worked close with other women

01:18:05.260 --> 01:18:13.260
and sometimes one event sticks in their mind like something they experienced the same time as somebody else.

01:18:13.260 --> 01:18:21.260
Like one of the girls up in the valleys, she said she remembers hearing my Rabber Van, that type of thing.

01:18:21.260 --> 01:18:22.260
Oh right, yeah.

01:18:22.260 --> 01:18:30.260
Another one was much older than you but she remembered hearing the Queen getting married on the radio.

01:18:30.260 --> 01:18:34.260
They stopped the factory and they played it on the radio for everybody to listen to.

01:18:35.260 --> 01:18:36.260
They'd done tools.

01:18:36.260 --> 01:18:44.260
Is there anything, any event that comes to mind when you think about the factory a particular day or anything like that?

01:18:44.260 --> 01:18:46.260
No, not really.

01:18:46.260 --> 01:18:50.260
The only thing we got in the factory on the town was when…

01:18:50.260 --> 01:18:55.260
Well Terry Griffiths, we were listening to Terry Griffiths winning his championship.

01:18:55.260 --> 01:18:57.260
And his wife was working…

01:18:57.260 --> 01:18:59.260
Lyn was working there at the time.

01:18:59.260 --> 01:19:00.260
Yeah, they put it all in the town.

01:19:00.260 --> 01:19:02.260
And that's the only thing we remember that.

01:19:02.260 --> 01:19:03.260
Oh right.

01:19:03.260 --> 01:19:05.260
That's the only thing we remember.

01:19:05.260 --> 01:19:06.260
There's nothing else, no?

01:19:06.260 --> 01:19:08.260
There's something coming over the town, no?

01:19:08.260 --> 01:19:09.260
Yeah, don't worry they never…

01:19:09.260 --> 01:19:12.260
What do you remember? A visit by anybody?

01:19:12.260 --> 01:19:14.260
No, nobody would recall it.

01:19:14.260 --> 01:19:16.260
I knew the Japanese coming round.

01:19:16.260 --> 01:19:19.260
That's normally a bad sign, isn't it?

01:19:19.260 --> 01:19:26.260
I know. And one of them went to pick up… what do you call them? They call them things, no men?

01:19:26.260 --> 01:19:31.260
They're red dots when you solder them and they stay red dot for a long time.

01:19:31.260 --> 01:19:36.260
And he went to pick it up and I went to tell him and I thought, oh too late.

